        <p><a href="http://gapersblock.com/tailgate/wcr-logo.png"><img alt="wcr-logo.png" src="http://gapersblock.com/tailgate/assets_c/2013/03/wcr-logo-thumb-150x150-11554.png" width="150" height="150" class="mt-image-left" style="float: left; margin: 0 20px 20px 0;" /></a> The <a href="http://www.windycityrollers.com/">Windy City Rollers</a> <a href="http://www.windycityrollers.com/travel-teams/wcr-all-stars/">All-Stars</a> beat the <a href="http://denverrollerdolls.org/skaters-staff/teams/mile-high-club/">Denver Roller Dolls Mile High Club</a> 138-132 Saturday to win the Golden Bowl III tournament. </p>

<p>Saturday's victory meant the All-Stars finished the tournament 3-0, while the other three teams - the Mile High Club, the <a href="http://www.texasrollergirls.org/teams-staff/texecutioners/">Texas Rollergirls Texecutioners</a> and the <a href="http://www.bayareaderbygirls.com/teams/golden-girls-all-stars">B.ay A.rea D.erby Girls Golden Girls</a> - finished with records of 1-2. Based on point differential, Denver finished second, Texas third and B.ay A.rea fourth.</p>
        <p>The All-Stars led 100-56 at the half, though the bout was not nearly as one-sided as the score might suggest. </p>

<p>Denver started the second half strong, chipping away at the lead until the score was 138-128 in favor of the All-Stars with 48 seconds left to play. Sami "Slamsonite" Lester took lead jammer for Denver in the final jam. The All-Stars' <a href="http://www.windycityrollers.com/members/yvette-yourmaker/">Yvette YourMaker</a> quickly went to the penalty box, giving Denver a power jam. </p>

<p>But the power jam didn't last long, as Lester soon went to the box, releasing Yvette YourMaker. The All-Stars managed to hold Lester to only four points after she was released from the penalty box, securing the win and the tournament title.</p>

<p>"It was fun to play - fun and nerve-wracking," All-Stars captain Bork Bork Bork said after the bout. "This was a big step forward for us as a team."</p>

<p>Though the All-Stars came out on top, Bork Bork Bork said the team could have done more to take advantage of the times when Denver's jammers were in the penalty box. </p>

<p>"Power jams, when giving to you, are a gift," she said.</p>

<p>Bork Bork Bork praised the All-Stars' efforts to stay out of the penalty box Saturday and said the score could have been different had Denver had fewer penalties or the All-Stars had more.</p>

<p>"Denver had a ton of penalties," she said. "Typically it's Windy (City Rollers) in that position. You never know. This game can change so quickly."</p>

<p>In other action Saturday, Texas beat Denver 227-189 to secure third place. The Rollers' c-team, the <a href="http://www.windycityrollers.com/travel-teams/third-coast/">Third Coast</a>, beat the St. Louis-based Arch Rival Roller Girls Fleur De Linquents 274-113.</p>
