        <p><a href="http://gapersblock.com/tailgate/wcr-logo.png"><img alt="wcr-logo.png" src="http://gapersblock.com/tailgate/assets_c/2013/03/wcr-logo-thumb-150x150-11554.png" width="150" height="150" class="mt-image-left" style="float: left; margin: 0 20px 20px 0;" /></a> Some of the top roller derby leagues in the world will converge on the UIC Pavilion tomorrow and Sunday when the <a href="http://www.windycityrollers.com/">Windy City Rollers</a> host Golden Bowl III.</p>

<p>The tournament will feature four of the top 10 derby leagues in the world, according to the <a href="http://wftda.com/rankings">Women's Flat Track Derby Association</a>. The <a href="http://www.windycityrollers.com/travel-teams/wcr-all-stars/">Windy City Rollers All-Stars</a>, as of June 30, are ranked 10th, while the <a href="http://denverrollerdolls.org/skaters-staff/teams/mile-high-club/">Denver Roller Dolls Mile High Club</a> are ranked 2nd. Also taking part in the tournament are the <a href="http://www.texasrollergirls.org/teams-staff/texecutioners/">Texas Rollergirls Texecutioners</a>, currently ranked 6th, and the 4th-ranked <a href="http://www.bayareaderbygirls.com/teams/golden-girls-all-stars">Bay Area Derby Girls Golden Girls</a>. </p>
        <p>Amy Hanson, also known as F.N. Fed and who skates for the Manic Attackers (one of WCR's home teams), helped plan the tournament and said it started two years ago by the Bay Area Derby Girls, along with Windy City and the Texas Rollergirls. The first year, the tournament was held in California and it was held in Texas under a different name last year, she said.</p>

<p>Hanson said that while Texas used a different name when they hosted last year, the committee that planned this year's event wanted to change it back.</p>

<p>"We're trying to bring it back to the name Golden Bowl," she said. </p>

<p>In addition to the tournament bouts, WCR's other travel teams - the <a href="http://www.windycityrollers.com/travel-teams/second-wind/">Second Wind</a> and <a href="http://www.windycityrollers.com/travel-teams/third-coast/">Third Coast</a> - will also play this weekend in between tournament bouts. The Second Wind faces off against Ontario's Tri-City Thunder tomorrow afternoon, while the Third Coast takes on the <a href="http://www.archrivalrollergirls.com/teams-staff/fdl/">Fleur-De-Linquents</a>, the c-team of the St. Louis-based Arch Rival Roller Girls.</p>

<p>This year's tournament will feature one thing that has not been seen in years past - a traveling trophy awarded to the winner. </p>

<p>"The trophy itself will be a golden bowl," Hanson said. <br />
<u><strong><br />
Golden Bowl III schedule (All bouts at the UIC Pavilion - 525 S. Racine)</strong></u><br />
<strong>DAY 1 (Saturday):</strong><br />
<ul><br />
	<li>NOON - Texas Rollergirls Texecutioners vs. WCR All-Stars</li><br />
	<li>1:55 p.m. - WCR Second Wind vs. Tri-City Thunder</li><br />
	<li>3:50 p.m. - Bay Area Derby Girls Golden Girls vs. Denver Roller Dolls Mile High Club</li><br />
	<li>5:45 p.m. - Junior Derby Expo</li><br />
	<li>7:00pm - WCR All-Stars vs. Bay Area Derby Girls Golden Girls</li><br />
</ul></p>

<p><strong>DAY 2 (Sunday):</strong><br />
<ul><br />
	<li>NOON - Bay Area Derby Girls Golden Girls vs. Texas Rollergirls Texecutioners</li><br />
	<li>1:55pm - WCR All-Stars vs. Denver Roller Dolls Mile High Club</li><br />
	<li>3:50pm - WCR Third Coast vs. Arch Rival Fleur de Linquents</li><br />
	<li>5:45pm - Texas Rollergirls Texecutioners vs. Denver Roller Dolls Mile High Club</li><br />
	</ul></p>
